We are writing to inform you of a critical escalation in corporate intimidation tactics following our international accountability campaign concerning sexual violence at Dongguk University's Graduate School of Digital Image and Contents. A strategic social media campaign documenting this crisis achieved viral status on Xiaohongshu (China's leading social platform), generating 26,611 total views and prompting victim testimonies. The campaign's success has now triggered escalated legal intimidation from film company Sidus, including professional law firm letterhead threats demanding immediate retraction, revealing the corporate infrastructure used to silence sexual violence victims.

